==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: perdurantist
<hw>per*dur"ant*ist</hw> <pr>(p⟦etil⟧r*d⟦umac⟧r"⟦ait⟧nt*⟦icr⟧st)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Philosophy)</fld> <def>A philosopher who considers
the fundamental objects of the real world as extended in the direction
of time, so that the objects themselves do not change, though temporal
parts may have different properties. Contrasted to
<contr>endurantist</contr>, one who considers objects to be wholly
present at each instant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perdure</ent>⟦br⟧
